    "title": "Fifty Ways To Leave Your Lover",
    "artist": "Paul Simon",
    "key": "",
    "isRTL": false,
    "rawText": "// Em/G D6 / CM7 B7b9 / Em EbO / F#m6 B7+ //\n// Em D6 / CM7 B7b9 / Em7 Am7 / Em //\n\n\n\nEm/G                 D6                     CM7                       B7b9\nThe problem is all inside your head, she said to me\nEm                   EbO              F#m6            B7+\nThe answer is easy if you take it logically\nEm           D6                         CM7                  B7b9\nI'd like to help you in your struggle to be free\n            B7     Em7      Am7                          Em\nThere must be Fifty ways to leave your lover\n\n\nEm/G           D6                    CM7            B7b9\nShe said it's really not my habit to intrude\nEm                                     EbO\nFurthermore I hope my meaning won't be\nF#m6                 B7+\nlost or misconstrued\n      Em                  D6              CM7                B7b9\nBut I'll repeat myself at the risk of being crude\n           B7        Em      Am7                           Em\nthere must be Fifty ways to leave your lover\n         Am7                         Em\nFifty ways to leave your lover\n\n\n                             G7                                    Bb\nJust slip out the back jack, make a new plan stan,\n                           C                                    G7\nNo need to be coy Roy, just listen to me\n                     G7                                    Bb\nHop on the bus gus, don't need to discuss much,\n                              C                                            G7\nJust drop off the key Lee, and set yourself free\n                             G7                                    Bb\nJust slip out the back jack, make a new plan stan,\n                           C                                    G7\nNo need to be coy Roy, just listen to me\n                     G7                                        Bb\nHop on the bus gus, don't need to discuss much,\n                              C                                            G\nJust drop off the key Lee, and set yourself free\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nEm/G        D6                         CM7                     B7b9\nShe said it grieves me so to see you in such pain\n                              Em                           EbO\nI wish there was something I could do\n     F#m6                     B7+\nto make you smile again\nEm         D6                             CM7                         B7b9\nI said I appreciate that and would you please explain\nB7              Em      Am7     Em\nAbout the fifty ways\n\n\nEm/G              D6                             CM7           B7b9\nShe said why don't we both just sleep on it tonight\n          Em                    EbO\nAnd I believe in the morning you'll\nF#m6                    B7+\nbegin to see the light\n                         Em                      D6\nAnd then she kissed me and\n  CM7                B7b9\nI realized she probably was right\n  B7                    Em    Am7                         Em\nthere must be Fifty ways to leave your lover\n         Am7                          Em\nFifty ways to leave your lover\n\n\n                             G7                                    Bb\nJust slip out the back jack, make a new plan stan,\n                           C                                    G7\nNo need to be coy Roy, just listen to me\n                     G7                                    Bb\nHop on the bus gus, don't need to discuss much,\n                              C                                            G7\nJust drop off the key Lee, and set yourself free\n                             G7                                    Bb\nJust slip out the back jack, make a new plan stan,\n                           C                                    G7\nNo need to be coy Roy, just listen to me\n                     G7                                        Bb\nHop on the bus gus, don't need to discuss much,\n                              C       